article.description: J.C. Show scored 14 points as Binghamton won its third straight, beating Colgate 73-64 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Show with 14 points as Binghamton beats Colgate 73-64
article.linkText: Show with 14 points as Binghamton beats Colgate 73-64
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- J.C. Show scored 14 points as Binghamton won its third straight, beating Colgate 73-64 on Wednesday night. Show was 4 of 6 from the field and 5 of 6 from the line for the Bearcats (7-4). Yosef Yacob added 13 points including four 3-pointers and Thomas Bruce had 11 points and four rebounds. The team averaged 53 percent shooting from the field and 65 percent from the line. Yacob's fourth 3-pointer gave the Bearcats their biggest lead, 64-44, with 6:05 to play after the team had led by nine points at the break. Colgate cut it to 69-62 with 42 seconds remaining but did not get closer. Four 3-pointers early in the first period helped launch Binghamton to a 22-8 lead midway and the Bearcats led 35-26 at intermission. Sean O'Brien scored 14 points with five rebounds and three assists for the Raiders (2-8) who are on a four-game skid.
